cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.IR, cs.CY 

This paper is likely to belong to the arXiv CS sub-category of cs.CL (Computation and Language) as it deals with sentiment classification in text data. It could also belong to cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) as it proposes a novel method for data augmentation and classification. Additionally, it could be categorized under cs.IR (Information Retrieval) as sentiment analysis is a common task in information retrieval. Finally, it could also be classified under cs.CY (Computers and Society) as it deals with the analysis of human emotions and discourse markers in text data.
